{"lemma":"قَبِيحَةٌ","slug":"قَبِيحَةٌ","root":"ق.ب.ح","root_slug":"ق-ب-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ب-ح","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35059"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"ugly"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"vile, bad, abominable"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/qa.biːħ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35059","headword_ar":"قَبِيحٌ","root":"qbH","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bad, evil, abominable, foul, unseemly, unsightly, ugly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hideous; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanN","text_ar":"حَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, Msb, K, &c.;) applied to a form, and to an action, (L,) and to anything: (T:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qibaAHN","text_ar":"قِبَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaAHaY","text_ar":"قَبَاحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboHaY","text_ar":"قَبْحَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyHapN","text_ar":"قَبِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaAy^iHu","text_ar":"قَبَايِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qibaAHN","text_ar":"قِبَاحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqapN qabiyHapN Al$~uxobi","text_ar":"نَاقَةٌ قَبِيحَةٌ الشُّخْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel having wide orifices to her teats."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqabiyHu","text_ar":"القَبِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is said to signify]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The extremity of the bone of the elbow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) so in the T; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iborap","text_ar":"اـِبْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is another small bone, the head of which is large, and the rest of it small, [the former, i. e. the head.] compactly joined to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyH","text_ar":"قَبِيح"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or [it is more correctly expl. as]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the extremity of the bone of the upper half of the arm, next the elbow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) the extremity next the shoulderjoint being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHasanu","text_ar":"الحَسَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because of the abundance of the flesh that is upon it: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the lower part of the upper half of the arm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the upper part being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHasanu","text_ar":"الحَسَنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Fr. TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyHaAni","text_ar":"قَبِيحَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two slender ends that are at the heads of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEaAni","text_ar":"ذِرَاعَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two bones of the fore arm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyH","text_ar":"قَبِيح"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place of junction"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bones"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the shank and the thigh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyHaAni","text_ar":"قَبِيحَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and it is also called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqabaAHu","text_ar":"القَبَاحُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) accord. to A'Obeyd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisoru qabiyHK","text_ar":"كِسْرُ قَبِيحٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, TA,) which is composed of two syn. words, one prefixed to the other, governing it in the gen. case, (L,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bone of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEid","text_ar":"سَاعِد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper half of the arm"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the part next the middle to the elbow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, TA; and thus it is expl. in the S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ksr","text_ar":"كسر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["L","T","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%82%D8%A8%D9%8A%D8%AD/","headword_ar":"قبيح","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23487#b581e3","body_html":"<span>القبيح: هو ما يكون متعلق الذم في العاجل والعقاب في الآجل.</span>"}]}}